win11-window-tiling — Fedora Workstation Edition
================================================

Windows 11-style window tiling for Fedora Workstation (GNOME).

This edition installs the Tiling Shell GNOME extension with Snap Assistant,
Fancy Zones layouts, and Super+Arrow keyboard shortcuts.

Requirements
------------

  Fedora Workstation with GNOME Shell 45 or newer.

Install
-------

  sudo dnf install ./win11-window-tiling-1.0.0-1.fc41.noarch.rpm

Setup
-----

  win11-tiling-setup

Log out and back in, then open Extensions and confirm Tiling Shell is enabled.

Usage
-----

  Super + Left/Right/Up/Down   Move focused window between tiles
  Drag window to top edge      Open Snap Assistant (layout picker)
  Drag to screen edges         Snap to halves or quarters
  Ctrl + drag                  Place window in a specific tile
  Alt + drag                   Span across multiple tiles

Settings: Extensions > Tiling Shell

Commands
--------

  win11-tiling-setup --status     Check install status
  win11-tiling-setup --uninstall  Remove extension from your user profile

Build from source (on Fedora)
-----------------------------

  cd fedora-workstation
  ./build.sh

